HEADWORD: benni
<hw>benni</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an East Indian annual erect herb
(<spn>Sesamum indicum</spn>); the source of <prod>sesame seed</prod> or
<prod>benniseed</prod> and <prod>sesame oil</prod>. Same as
<er>benne</er></def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> sesame, benne, benny.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

